  "title": "'THE FAMILY CROW': A Murder Mystery",
  "description": "A mysterious murder has rocked the Family Crow! Enter Horatio P. Corvus - Sorter Outer of Murders! Puppets, puns, and plot twists abound in this award-winning international Fringe hit. Starring Adam Francis Proulx (Netflix, CBC, Nickelodeon). “Weird, cuckoo brilliance!” – Liz Nicholls",
  "credits": "<strong>Director</strong>: Byron Laviolette<br/><strong>Cast</strong>: Adam Francis Proulx<br/>",
  "website": "https://crowshow.ca",
  "plain_language": "This show is about a murder that happens in a family of crows. One crow, named Horatio P. Corvus, is a detective. He tries to figure out who committed the crime. The show is performed with a puppet. It is funny and full of wordplay and surprises. One person plays all the characters. It is a mix of comedy and mystery. If you like puppet shows, murder stories, or solving puzzles, you will enjoy this show.",
